lots for a given bluff-body position. Further, the suppression strategy\nalso depends on the spatial distribution of perforations on the bluff-body.\nNotably, an inappropriate distribution of the slots which does not quench the\nlocal heat release rate fluctuations at the stagnation zone may even result in\na dramatic increase in amplitudes of pressure oscillations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jan 2022 06:18:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-12"}
